solution: ```class Solution {
    public int findTheLongestBalancedSubstring(String s) {
        int max = 0;
        int n = s.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            int zeros = 0, ones = 0;
            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {
                if (s.charAt(j) == '0') {
                    if (ones == 0) zeros++;
                    else break;
                } else {
                    ones++;
                }
                if (zeros == ones) max = Math.max(max, j - i + 1);
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterate over every start index and expand rightwards while maintaining counts of consecutive 0s followed by 1s; whenever counts match, update the maximum length. Early-exit on any 0 that appears after a 1 keeps the inner loop tight.

